<SLUG> BC-CABBIE-ARREST-KAN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
CABDRIVER HELPS LEAD TO ARREST OF ROBBERY SUSPECT 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By CHRISTINE VENDEL  
 c. 1999 Kansas City Star  
<TEXT>
<P>
   KANSAS CITY, Mo. _ A cabdriver who was robbed two weeks ago may
have saved another cabbie from the same fate and helped police
arrest a Kansas City man, police said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   Fredrick E. Hardy, 23, was arraigned Wednesday on two counts of
first-degree robbery. He was in jail Wednesday night on a $75,000
bond.
</P>
<P>
   This is what happened, according to the cabdriver and court
records:
</P>
<P>
   On May 20, the driver, Jerry Bussey, picked up a man in the 1600
block of Elmwood. The rider pointed a gun at Bussey's head and
demanded money. Bussey gave the robber $84 and the robber ran.
</P>
<P>
   After he was robbed, Bussey asked his dispatcher to notify him
if other calls sounded suspicious. Eleven days later, the
dispatcher did.
</P>
<P>
   Bussey drove to a convenience store at 19th Street and Jackson
Avenue and recognized a man standing at the door. Bussey parked
behind the store and walked to the front door.
</P>
<P>
   The man held the door open for Bussey as he entered and left the
store.
</P>
<P>
   Bussey then returned to his cab and called his dispatcher at
Checker Cab.
</P>
<P>
   Bussey said he told the dispatcher, ``This guy doesn't need a
taxi. He needs a paddy wagon.''
</P>
<P>
   About that time a Yellow Cab driver had pulled up to get gas and
the man asked for a ride. But Bussey pulled his car in front of the
Yellow Cab and gave the other driver a coded signal that the man
might be dangerous.
</P>
<P>
   The two drivers stalled until police arrived. The man went into
the store, where officers arrested him. They later found a gun
hidden inside.
</P>
<P>
   When questioned, Hardy denied involvement in the robbery.
</P>
<P>
   Police said he also was suspected of robbing a cabdriver May 29
at Truman Road and Hardesty Avenue and was being investigated in
three other recent cases in the same area.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-06-03-99 0049EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
