<SLUG> BC-RAC-BELMONT-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
CHARISMATIC DRAWING CROWD
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By RANDY MOSS 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   ELMONT, N.Y. _ Charismatic might be running for the Triple Crown
on Saturday, but his competition isn't running away.
</P>
<P>
   Twelve 3-year-olds were entered Wednesday for the 11/2-mile
Belmont Stakes, in which Kentucky Derby and Preakness winner
Charismatic will bid to become the first horse since 1978 to sweep
the grueling three-race series.
</P>
<P>
   Of the 26 horses that have gone into the Belmont with a chance
to win a Triple Crown, only one faced a larger field. Thirteen
started when Canonero II finished fourth in 1971.
</P>
<P>
   ``Bring them on, bring them all on,'' said Bob Lewis, the
Newport Beach, Calif., beer distributor who owns the colt with his
wife, Beverly.
</P>
<P>
   At least Charismatic has finally won the oddsmakers over.
</P>
<P>
   After being 15-1 on the program line for the Kentucky Derby and
dismissed at 6-1 for the Preakness, he was made the 2-1 early
favorite for the Belmont.
</P>
<P>
   If he wins the Belmont, Charismatic will become the first horse
to earn the $5 million VISA Triple Crown Challenge bonus. Aside
from that, the Belmont is a $1 million race, with $600,000 going to
the winner.
</P>
<P>
   Menifee, second to Charismatic in the first two legs, is next at
7-2 in the program line. Once-beaten Silverbulletday is 4-1, even
though she is running against males for the first time. No filly
has won the Belmont since Tanya in 1905.
</P>
<P>
   ``The filly will add a great deal of spice,'' Charismatic
trainer D. Wayne Lukas conceded. ``Half the world is women. She'll
have a built-in rooting section.''
</P>
<P>
   Others entered Wednesday were Best of Luck (6-1), Stephen Got
Even (10-1), Vision and Verse, Lemon Drop Kid, Patience Game and
Adonis (each 20-1); Pineaff and Prime Directive (30-1) and
Teletable (99-1).
</P>
<P>
   Charismatic got post No. 4 in the traditional-style draw in
which the positions are assigned at random and owners and trainers
have no choice. Menifee will start from No. 10 and Silverbulletday
drew No. 3.
</P>
<P>
   Because of the 11/2-mile distance, Belmont Park's sweeping turns
and the slightly shorter field, post positions in the Belmont
Stakes don't mean as much as the first two legs of the Triple
Crown.
</P>
<P>
   Charismatic and Silverbulletday arrived at Belmont Park at about
10:45 a.m. Wednesday on a flight from Louisville, Ky., that was
delayed 90 minutes because of stormy weather. MENIFEE PUTS IN FAST
WORKOUT
</P>
<P>
   Charismatic and Silverbulletday got most of the attention
Tuesday with their Churchill Downs workouts, but Menifee had a good
one of his own, too.
</P>
<P>
   At Belmont Park, Menifee zipped five furlongs in 59 seconds and
galloped out six furlongs in 1:112/5 _ the identical clockings as
Silverbulletday got in Kentucky.
</P>
<P>
   ``It was actually a little faster than I wanted,'' trainer
Elliott Walden said. ``But he went easy. He's a talented horse, and
he's doing great.''
</P>
<P>
   Walden had Menifee flown from Kentucky to Belmont earlier than
his rivals to familiarize him with the deeper and sandier surface.
</P>
<P>
   ``It looks like he handles this racetrack pretty well,'' Walden
said.
</P>
<P>
   Walden used similar tactics last year with Victory Gallop, also
second in the Derby and Preakness. That colt won the Belmont to
spoil Real Quiet's Triple Crown bid. BITING THE HAND THAT...
</P>
<P>
   After the Preakness victory two weeks ago, Lukas commented that
Charismatic was feeling cockier than ever.
</P>
<P>
   ``He even bit Bob Lewis,'' Lukas said.
</P>
<P>
   It turns out that Charismatic gave his owner more than just a
playful nip. Perhaps as a payback for twice running him in a
claiming race, he took a hunk out of Lewis' hand, and 10 stitches
were needed to close the wound.
</P>
<P>
   Lewis, a World War II sergeant, laughed off the incident.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm just keeping my hands to myself from now on,'' he said.
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
