   WELFARE-ECONSCENE (Undated) _ Proponents of the 1996 welfare law
are finding plenty of reasons to feel smug these days. So should
opponents, including several high-ranking administration officials
who resigned when President Clinton signed the Republican-sponsored
bill, acknowledge they were wrong? ``No,'' says Wendell Primus of
the Center on Budget and Policy Priorities.
</P>
<P>
   WATER-AD-COLUMN (Undated) _ Robert F. Kennedy Jr. and others are
marketing Keeper Springs Mountain Spring Water to finance efforts
to preserve and protect local waterways nationwide. By Patricia
Winters Lauro.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; CULTURE (Moved in ``e'' category) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ELVIS-AUCTION (Undated) _ More than 2,000 of Elvis Presley's
most treasured possessions _ among them clothes, furniture and
letters from Marilyn Monroe, Frank Sinatra, Marlon Brando and
President John F. Kennedy _ are to go on the auction block in
October in Las Vegas, in a sale of memorabilia from the archives of
Elvis' Graceland compound. By Felicia R. Lee.
</P>
<P>
   SOUTHBANK-RENEWAL (London) _ London's forbidding South Bank
Center is up for renewal. By Warren Hoge.
