<P>
   TRAVEL-PIGEONFORGE _ PIGEON FORGE, Tenn. _ The people who come
to Pigeon Forge, Tenn., and enjoy it _ including those folks in
folding chairs by the side of the road are unapologetic in their
pursuit of populist pleasure. Purist Tourists. They love this Bible
Belt Las Vegas, a city of spontaneous gernation that plopped out of
the Smokies three decades ago like Darwin's fish sprouting legs. A
working man's Magic Kingdom. As a tourist destination, it provokes
sharply polarized feelings; just mention the place in a crowd and
see how may eyes roll. Although the community sits smack in the
middle of one of the South's most profoundly spritual sights _ the
Smoky Mountains rising through the mist like silent humpback whales
there's virtually nothing natural within the Pigeon Forge city
limits. (M. Longino, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Embargoed for Sunday, June 6.
</P>
