<P>
   PEARL _ Something more precious than catfish and spotted bass is
growing in the clean, green waters of Kentucky Lake. They're
lustrous and adorn necks of women and the fingers of aristocrats
and potentates around the world. They're Tennessee's home-grown
pearls, cultivated from freshwater mussels that thrive in the vast
TVA lake near this west Tennessee town where Patsy Cline perished
in a l963 plane crash. The ``Pearl of a Tour'' takes visitors
through a detailed course in pearl cultivation. (Pousner, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) WITH PHOTO
</P>
