 ATTENTION EDITORS: Please note the different availability dates and
times for each page. 
 Here is an updated budget for the Focus, Nascar and Entertainment
pages, which will be available to clients by 2 p.m. or 5 p.m.
Thursday June 3 or by 2 p.m. Friday June 4, 1999:
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; FOCUS (available by 2 p.m., Fri., June 4) &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   PAGE INCLUDES AT LEAST THREE COLOR PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   WINDMILLS: Dusk was still several hours away as Ken O'Brock
tightened the final screws on the windmill he had constructed on a
sweltering spring day in a rolling pasture about 75 miles northwest
of Birmingham, Ala.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm doing twice as many jobs this year,'' said the owner and
installer of O'Brock Windmills of North Benton, Ohio. ``In one
week, I put up four windmills. One near Athens, Ga. One outside of
Bainbridge, Ga. And two in Florida.''
</P>
<P>
   Why this surprising surge in a centuries-old technology? Credit
a more modern technological glitch _ the Y2K bug. (Includes at
least three color photos.)
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NASCAR (Available by 5 p.m. Thu., June 3) &LR;  &QL;
</P>
