</P>
<P>
   WITH: BOONDOCKS: As far as race is concerned, Aaron McGruder
knew that his strip ``The Boondocks'' would ruffle some feathers.
That's because McGruder makes punch lines out of, well, touchy
subjects. (Includes 1-column color illustration from comic strip.)
</P>
<P>
   WITH: ALIENS RE-RELEASE: Twenty years after we learned an
acoustical fact about screaming in space, Fox is re-releasing the
four ``Alien'' movies in three formats. Here are reviews of the
films. (Includes 18-pica color photo from ``Alien Resurrection.'')
</P>
<P>
   WITH: VIDEO REVIEWS: Your twee alarm may go off at the very idea
of ``Waking Ned Devine.'' It's the tale of a small Irish village
where Ned, the new winner of a $7 million lottery ticket, has died
of shock.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: CD REVIEWS: The idea of blending a mostly straight-ahead
jazz approach to the work of reggae giant Bob Marley may seem
ghastly. But pianist Monty Alexander has pulled it off. Also,
``Lilith Fair Vols. 2 and 3.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
