<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Pigeon Forge if you go
 &HT;    EDs: Embargoed for Sunday, June 6.
 &HT;    Staff reports
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QR;  Getting there: It's 227 miles from downtown Atlanta to Pigeon
Forge, and the best way to get there is by car. Take I-75 north
through Chattanooga to Knoxville. Merge into I-40 East to Exit 407,
Sevierville/Gatlin-
</P>
<P>
   burg/Pigeon Forge. Exit right onto U.S. 66, which turns into
U.S. 441. It is 15 miles from the interstate to Pigeon Forge.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Lodging: There are 7,489 rooms in about 80 motels,
campgrounds, bed-and-breakfast inns, condos and rental cottages.
Request a 1999 Pigeon Forge Travel Planner by calling
1-800-251-9100.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  For more information: Go to the Pigeon Forge Department of
Tourism's official Web site at www.pigeon-forge.tn.us. For
information on the Great Smoky Mountains National Park, including
seasonal events, call 423-436-1200.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Attractions, dining:
</P>
<P>
   Lee Greenwood Theater, 2450 Winfield Dunn Parkway, Kodak, Tenn.
$24, 12 and under free. Shows 8 p.m. Mondays-Saturdays.
1-800-686-5471.
</P>
<P>
   LG's (Lee Greenwood's restaurant), 2450 Winfield Dunn Parkway,
Kodak. Open 11 a.m.-9 p.m. daily. Sunday brunch 11 a.m.-3 p.m.
($12.95). 423-932-6732.
</P>
<P>
   Alan Jackson's Showcar Cafe, 2301 Parkway. Open 8 a.m.-10 p.m.
daily. 423-908-9007.
</P>
<P>
   Applewood Farmhouse Restaurant, 230 Apple Valley Road,
Sevierville. Open 9 a.m.-7 p.m. Mondays-Thursdays, 9 a.m.-9 p.m.
Fridays-Saturdays, 10:30 a.m.-7 p.m. Sundays. 423-453-9319.
</P>
<P>
   Hill-Billy Village, 2898 Parkway. Open 9 a.m.-11 p.m. daily.
423-453-4153.
</P>
<P>
   Carbo's Police Museum, 3311 Parkway. Open 10 a.m.-5 p.m. daily.
Adults $5.88, children 10 and under $2.94. 423-453-1358.
</P>
<P>
   The Alabama Grill, 2050 Parkway. Open 11 a.m.-11 p.m. daily.
Closes at 10 p.m. Sundays. 423-908-8777.
</P>
<P>
   The Comedy Barn, 2775 Parkway, $16.95, children 11 and under
free. Shows daily at 5 and 8:15 p.m. 1-800-295-2844 or
423-428-5222.
</P>
<P>
   Tastebuds Cafe, 1198 Ware's Valley Road. Open 11:30 a.m.-2 p.m.
for lunch. Dinner served 5-9:30 p.m. Closed Sundays-Mondays.
Reservations required. 423-428-9781.
</P>
<P>
   Louise Mandrell Theater, 2046 Parkway. $23.98, children 11 and
under $9.95. Shows 7:30 p.m. Tuesdays-Saturdays. 423-453-6263.
</P>
<P>
   Robert F. Thomas Church in the Valley, inside Dollywood on
Middle Creek Road. Services 9:30 and 11:30 a.m. Sundays.
</P>
<P>
   Country Tonite, 129 Showplace Blvd., $23.15, teens half-price,
children 12 and under free. Shows 3 and 8 p.m. Tuesdays-Sundays.
1-800-792-4308 or 423-453-2003.
</P>
<P>
   Eddie's Heart &AMP; Soul Cafe, 140 Showplace Blvd., featuring the
Blackwood Quartet. $18.99 breakfast show, $20.99 dinner show
(children 6-10 half-price). Breakfast shows 8:30 a.m.
Tuesdays-Fridays. Dinner shows 7 p.m. Sundays-Mondays.
423-453-0833.
</P>
