<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SHARPS-COLUMN-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
THE REAL THING FROM RANDY NEWMAN
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By FRED SHUSTER  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Of the sometimes autobiographical material on his
new album, Randy Newman says he's both ``seen it and lived it.''
</P>
<P>
   The collection, produced by Mitchell Froom and Tchad Blake,
depicts an aging man hooked on a young girl, a fossilized rock star
who doesn't know when to quit and a seemingly nice, sentimental
fellow who only wants to be liked. And, of course, there's an open
letter to Karl Marx.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm not usually talking about anyone specifically in the
songs,'' Newman said before last weekend's three-night stand at the
House of Blues. ``I mean, like the number (``Shame'') about the old
guy on the hook to a young woman _ I'm not involved in something
like that. But it can be amusing, and I've always found it
interesting to observe across a room.''
</P>
<P>
   The disc, ``Bad Love'' (DreamWorks), is only the most recent
highlight in what's been a good year for the sardonic
singer-songwriter. Last fall, ``Guilty: 30 Years of Randy Newman''
(Warner Archive), a four-disc anthology featuring the cream of his
album and motion-picture work, was issued to widespread acclaim.
</P>
<P>
   Earlier this year, the Grammy- and Emmy-winning composer was
nominated for three Academy Awards, in three music categories, for
the films ``Pleasantville,'' ``A Bug's Life'' and ``Babe: Pig in
the City.''
</P>
<P>
   Although he's been nominated for a dozen Oscars, Newman has yet
to win one of the coveted statuettes. Not that he minds much.
</P>
<P>
   ``It sounds like a cliche _ but the work itself is its own
reward,'' Newman, 55, said. ``Not winning an Oscar isn't something
that breaks my heart.''
</P>
<P>
   Now working on the sequel to ``Toy Story,'' Newman says he
prefers short solo tours to long treks with a band.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm not band-oriented,'' he explained. ``Maybe what's best
about me are the songs, unadorned.''
</P>
<P>
   Sounds right to us. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-06-03-99 1407EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
