<P>
   &UR; KOSOVO &LR;
</P>
<P>
   (A separate KOSOVO-ADVISORY has already moved.)
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-PEACE-PLAN (Belgrade, Yugoslavia) _ Slobodan Milosevic
and the Serbian parliament accept draft accord for peace; document
calls for all Serbian forces to leave Kosovo and an international
force with an ``essential'' role for NATO in the province. Serb
withdrawal may start Sunday. NATO generals expected to come to
Belgrade within days. Bombing expected to stop then if not earlier.
By Steven Erlanger.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-MILOSEVIC (Belgrade, Yugoslavia) _ News Analysis on
Milosevic and what he got out of _ or didn't get out of _ the
latest peace proposal. By Steven Erlanger.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-U.S.-REAX (Washington) _ U.S. reaction to peace
developments in Yugoslavia: National Security Council says it looks
like ``the real thing.'' By John Broder and Jane Perlez.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-PROBLEMS (Washington) _ What now: The problems that lie
ahead. By Serge Schmemann.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-RUSSIA (Moscow) _ The Russian role in the peace deal. By
Michael R. Gordon.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-REFUGEE-REAX (Dateline and byline to be determined) _
Refugee reaction to the peace deal.
</P>
<P>
   In addition, the Times is working on European reaction to the
peace proposal; what the Kosovo Liberation Army has to say; the
mood in Belgrade to developments; fresh details on the NATO
peacekeeping force that would go into Kosovo; where the aid money
to reconstruct will come from, and military developments.
</P>
<P>
   We also plan to have several graphics. They tentatively include
highlights of the peace plan; a comparison with the proposal drawn
up in Rambouillet, France, in February; and up-to-date numbers on
refugees, casualties, bombing runs, etc.
</P>
