with his top military officers to discuss possible ground invasion
scenarios in Kosovo, as word comes from Belgrade of the
Parliament's acceptance of a proposed peace plan delivered to
Yugoslav President Slobodan Milosevic by Russia's special envoy to
the Balkans Viktor Chernomyrdin and Finland President Martti
Ahtisaari. Developing. (Deans, Cox News Service)
