died last month in the jail of a blow to the head. The detective
who investigated the case said he doesn't believe anyone struck
Campos _ who was kept isolated during his two-week stay due to
severe symptoms of alchohol withdrawal _ but he called
``questionable'' the four hours that Campos was left lying on the
floor of his cell before jailers called an ambulance. The Mexican
consulate is investigating at the request of Campos' family, who
mostly declined to comment. (Quinn, Austin American-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
   C130 _ WASHINGTON _ This is a tale of getting what you want. The
Pentagon asked for 0 C-130J transport planes in its budget request.
Lockheed Martin, which makes the plane in Marietta, said, ``Are you
sure?'' The Pentagon said, ``Yes, thank you, we're sure.'' So now
it looks as though the next budget will include money for at least
4 and maybe as many as 7 of the $60 million planes. That's what can
happen when a powerful Democrat decides his local National Guard
unit absolutely needs one and the Senate Majority Leader discovers
a crying need for two in (guess where?) Mississippi. (Sherman,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED
