<P>
   TAX-SHELTERS (Washington) _ Concerned about keeping ahead of the
blizzard of tax-avoidance strategies being developed and marketed
by accountants and lawyers to corporate clients, the Clinton
administration has asked Congress for broad new powers to
discourage the use of tax shelters. In the process, the
administration has set off a sharp debate in Congress and among
accountants and tax lawyers over how big a problem there is and the
degree to which giving the IRS more power is the solution. By
Richard W. Stevenson.
</P>
<P>
   ROCHE-GENENTECH (San Francisco) _ Roche Holding plans to buy the
third of Genentech Inc. it does not already own in a deal it values
at $4.2 billion, then sell as much as 19 percent of the
biotechnology company to the public. By Lawrence M. Fisher.
</P>
<P>
   RETAIL-EARNINGS (Undated) _ The nation's largest retail chains
report robust sales for May, exceeding analysts' forecasts. By
Michael T. Kaufman.
</P>
<P>
   MICROSOFT-ANTITRUST (Washington) _ Microsoft showed its hand in
court Thurdday, entering into evidence several documents it will
use in an effort to impeach the testimony of key Justice Department
witnesses later this month. By Joel Brinkley.
</P>
<P>
   WTO-BEEF-SANCTION (Geneva) _ A trans-Atlantic fight over
hormone-treated beef intensified Thursday when American and
Canadian officials asked the World Trade Organization to approve
$253 million in retaliatory trade sanctions, and the European Union
countered by demanding arbitration it hopes will lower the overall
amount. By Elizabeth Olson.
</P>
<P>
   CHINA-YUAN (Shanghai) _ China clamps down on overseas
transactions in the yuan in an effort to restrict local currency
flows in and out of the country. The disclosure of the new rules
roils Asian markets, as traders fear that the move is a precursor
to a devaluation of the currency. But China's central bank later
denies that a devaluation is imminent. By Seth Faison.
</P>
<P>
   AMTRAK-AD-COLUMN (Undated) _ Amtrak introduces a new campaign
for its Northeast routes. By Stuart Elliott.
</P>
<P>
   COMPANIES (Undated) _ Company news.
</P>
<P>
   KEYRATES (Undated) _ Key interest rate numbers.
</P>
<P>
   BIZGLANCE (Undated) _ Major financial stories at a glance.
</P>
