   &UR; THE FACE OF `COLLATERAL DAMAGE' &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; By ROBERT FISK, The Independent of London &LR;  &QC; 
 &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   SURDULICA, CENTRAL SERBIA _ Not far from Milena Malobabic's
young body, we found the notebook of love poems she wrote for her
boyfriend.
</P>
<P>
   NATO's jets had killed her and at least 18 other patients in the
tuberculosis sanatorium just a few hours earlier and Milena's body
lay in the shade of a pine tree, her long black hair drifting over
her face in the breeze, a silver earring still sparkling in her
left ear.
</P>
<P>
   NATO's bombs destroyed a hospital Monday and they called it _
heaven spare us again _ ``collateral damage.'' But Milena's death
alone constitutes a unique tragedy of war... &QL;
</P>
