<HEADLINE>
ARTICHOKES WITH LIGHT HONEY MUSTARD DIP 

</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  (Eds.: Also see: Food-artichoke) 
c.1999 Houston Chronicle 
 
4 medium artichokes 
1 teaspoon salt 
1/2 cup reduced-fat mayonnaise 
2 teaspoons honey 
1/2 teaspoon each: prepared mustard and fresh lemon juice 
 
Wash artichokes under cold running water. Cut off stem at base;
remove small bottom leaves. If desired, trim tips of leaves and cut
off top 2 inches. Stand artichokes upright in large nonreactive
saucepan. Add salt and 2 to 3 inches boiling water. Cover and boil
gently 35 to 45 minutes or until base can be pierced easily with a
fork. Add a little more boiling water if needed. Drain artichokes
upside down. Serve immediately. Or cool completely, cover and
refrigerate to chill. Makes 4 servings.
<TEXT>
<P>
   To make dip, combine mayonnaise, honey, mustard and lemon juice;
mix well. Makes about 1/2 cup.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
CREAMY THAI DIP &QL; 
 &QL; 
1/4 cup each: creamy peanut butter and firmly packed brown sugar &QL; 
2 tablespoons each: cider vinegar and soy sauce &QL; 
1 teaspoon sesame oil &QL; 
1/8 teaspoon ground ginger &QL; 
Combine peanut butter, brown sugar, vinegar, soy sauce, oil and
ginger; mix well. Makes about 3/4 cup.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &QL; 
Variation:  &LR; For Oriental Dip, omit peanut butter.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
TANGY MAYONNAISE &QL; 
 &QL; 
From ``The California Artichoke Cookbook'' by Mary Comfort, Noreen
Griffee and Charlene Walker (Celestial Arts, $4.95). &QL; 
 &QL; 
1 1/3 cups mayonnaise &QL; 
1/4 cup cider vinegar &QL; 
2 tablespoons milk &QL; 
1 tablespoon each: sugar and grated onion &QL; 
2 teaspoons prepared mustard &QL; 
1/2 teaspoon each: ground celery seed and salt &QL; 
1/8 teaspoon ground black pepper &QL; 
Blend mayonnaise with vinegar, milk, sugar, onion, mustard, celery
seed, salt and pepper; mix well. Makes about 1 3/4 cups.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Variations: &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Herb: &LR;  Add 1/4 teaspoon each: tarragon and basil.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Aoli: &LR;  Add 1 garlic clove, minced
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Caper: &LR;  Add 2 tablespoons drained, chopped capers.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
GREEK-STYLE GARBANZO DIP &QL; 
 &QL; 
1 (15 1/2-ounce) can reduced sodium garbanzo beans (chickpeas) &QL; 
1/4 cup fresh lemon juice &QL; 
1 teaspoon minced garlic &QL; 
1 1/2 teaspoons olive oil &QL; 
1/2 teaspoon grated lemon zest (thinnest colored part of peel
only) &QL; 
2 tablespoons finely chopped parsley &QL; 
3 tablespoons thinly sliced green onion &QL; 
1/4 teaspoon crushed dried oregano &QL; 
 &QL; 
Drain beans; reserve 6 tablespoons liquid. In blender or food
processor, place beans, reserved liquid, lemon juice, garlic and
oil. Cover and process until smooth. Transfer mixture to a bowl and
stir in lemon zest, parsley, green onion and oregano. Cover and
refrigerate until ready to use. Makes 1 1/2 cups.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Serves 4 as a dip with artichokes, each serving: 212 calories,
11 grams protein, 37 grams carbohydrates; 4 grams fat, no
cholesterol, 8 grams fiber, 124 milligrams sodium. &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
PATIO ARTICHOKE SUPPER &QL; 
 &QL; 
1/4 cup chopped green onion &QL; 
2 tablespoons each: slivered almonds, chopped cilantro and olive
oil &QL; 
6 ounces angel hair pasta, cooked according to package directions &QL; 
1 1/2 cups diced cooked or smoked turkey &QL; 
1 tablespoon fresh lime juice &QL; 
1/2 teaspoon salt &QL; 
1/4 teaspoon ground black pepper &QL; 
4 cooked artichokes &QL; 
Fresh Salsa (recipe follows) &QL; 
 &QL; 
Saute onion, almonds and cilantro in oil until almonds are browned.
Add cooked pasta, turkey, lime juice, salt and pepper. Cook and
toss until thoroughly heated. Carefully scrape out fuzzy center
portion of cooked artichokes with a small spoon and discard. Fill
artichokes with pasta mixture. Spoon Fresh Salsa on pasta filling
and between petals of artichokes.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Makes 4 servings, each: 271 calories, 22.9 grams protein, 10.7
grams fat, 29.3 grams carbohydrates, 38 milligrams cholesterol, 6
grams fiber, 700 milligrams sodium. &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
FRESH SALSA &QL; 
 &QL; 
2 cups diced tomatoes &QL; 
1/2 cup chopped green pepper &QL; 
1/4 cup each, chopped: Anaheim pepper and green onions &QL; 
2 tablespoons chopped cilantro &QL; 
4 teaspoons fresh lime juice &QL; 
1 teaspoon garlic salt &QL; 
1/2 teaspoon crushed dried oregano &QL; 
1/4 teaspoon bottled hot red pepper sauce &QL; 
Combine tomatoes, green pepper, Anaheim pepper, green onion,
cilantro, lime juice, garlic salt, oregano and pepper sauce; mix
well. Makes about 3 cups.
</P>
<P>
