   Moving in (w) Washington and (f) financial categories.
</P>
<P>
   DEPOT-LIGHTING _ATLANTA _ Home Depot will acquire privately held
Georgia Lighting, and Atlanta-based retailer with six stores. Terms
were not disclosed. Home Depot said that Georgia Lighting's
expertise would strengthen its merchandising. Current management
will continue to operate Georgia LIghting showrooms. (Bond, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   ATLANTA-CONVENTIONS _ The Atlanta Convention &AMP; Visitors Bureau
wants to boost the city's image as an international city. In
September, the ACVB will team up with its counterparts in
Cincinnati and New York and Delta Air Lines to sponsor a three-day
trade show targeting 120 of the largest European meeting and
convention planners. (Poole, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   IXL-IPO _ IXL is supposed to go public today or tomorrow. We
take a close look at the emergence of this company and how the IPO
works and fares in the market. (Katz, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   MADISON _Investors who got burned buying stock in two
high-flying micro-cap companies may get some relief. The SEC has
petitioned a court to return nearly $3 million to shareholders. If
the U.S. District Court in New York agrees, the SEC will seek
refunds for investors in Citron and Electronic Transfer Associates,
tapping $2.5 million in a New York brokerage account tied to
Glittergrove Investments, an offshore corporation. (Clothier,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   MINDSPRING _MindSpring strikes deal with Barnes and Noble.
BN.com will have presence on MSPG homepage and members will get
special offers and deal (Katz, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   PBP-ONLINE _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ With on-line investing as
trendy as company names ending in dot-com, two Boca Raton firms aim
to cash in on the rise of electronic stock trading.
Onlinetradinginc.com plans its initial stock offering Tuesday.
Meanwhile, Frost Hanna Capital Group will target on-line investors
with its planned purchase of a Long Island brokerage. Both
companies say the explosion of on-line trading will translate to
profits. But are they jumping on the trend too late? (Ostrowski,
Palm Beach Post).
</P>
<P>
   PBP-PAXSON (DEVELOPING) _ A folo on Paxson Communications' deal
to create a health program that could be a prelude to a 24-hour
health network. (Sedore, Palm Beach Post)
</P>
