<P>
   CALIFORNIA-BEE. Anu Gollapudi, a 12-year-old from Walnut, knew
something was wrong as soon as the pronouncer from the national
spelling bee asked her to spell a word she had never heard before.
After requesting a definition, Gollapudi spelled the word
``Yarborough'' incorrectly and was eliminated from the 72nd annual
competition. (180 words.) By Mark Stricherz
</P>
