<P>
   UNDATED _ Next Tuesday, Thomas Harris will unleash Hannibal
Lecter on the world for the third time. ``Hannibal,'' published by
Dell, is the eagerly anticipated sequel to ``The Silence of the
Lambs,'' the bestseller that sent chills through a nation of
readers. Known for coolly devouring his victims while enjoying a
glass of fine wine, Hannibal the Cannibal clearly ranks among the
most evil characters in all of literature _ but he has plenty of
company. Here is a list of the 10 scariest literary monsters of all
time. It is not for the squeamish. By JEFF GUINN. Story will move
in ``e'' entertainment category. &QL; 
