<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SEAL04-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    20 questions for Seal
 &HT;    By Sonia Murray
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Born Sealhenri Samuels, the British pop star known as
Seal has used his commanding voice and formidable physique (6 feet
</P>
<P>
   4 inches with a shaved head) to cut an impressive figure
throughout the 1990s. In 1994, his single ``Kiss From a Rose''
became the title song for the movie ``Batman Forever.'' In 1996,
Seal won Grammy Awards for best record, song and male pop vocal.
</P>
<P>
   Shortly before the London-born son of Nigerian immigrants
started his current tour in Las Vegas, we asked the 36-year-old
vocalist to play ``20 Questions,'' with one caveat: simple
responses, please.
</P>
<P>
   Q:What don't you say often enough?
</P>
<P>
   A:``I love you.'' I don't think you can say that enough.
</P>
<P>
   Q:What is your greatest regret?
</P>
<P>
   A:I don't really have one.
</P>
<P>
   Q:Even about your current record? (``Human Being,'' which has
fallen from Billboard magazine's Top 200 chart after peaking at No.
22.)
</P>
<P>
   A:I'm pleased with the record, in terms of my integrity as an
artist being maintained. Obviously, a little more commercial
success would be lovely. But I'm happy with what I did and the way
that I was able to say it. And the opportunity that I had to say
it.
</P>
<P>
   Q:What is your greatest fear?
</P>
<P>
   A:That we will never overcome as humans our differences that
make us go to war.
</P>
<P>
   Q:OK, let's try something a little lighter. What would the Seal
special be in a restaurant?
</P>
<P>
   A:Bresaola.
</P>
<P>
   Q:And that is ...
</P>
<P>
   A:A thinly sliced beef Italian dish. It's usually served with
arugula, lemon and olive oil. It's what I tend to eat when I go to
a restaurant. I'm an O blood type, and we are serious meat eaters!
</P>
<P>
   Q:What do you have to have in your refrigerator?
</P>
<P>
   A:Water. Well, no, I like to have that at room temperature. So
I'll say turkey sausages.
</P>
<P>
   Q:Which talent would you most like to have?
</P>
<P>
   A:I would like to be a great public speaker. I enjoy
communication. That's the one area I enjoy most: communication and
understanding.
</P>
<P>
   Q:What is the trait you most deplore in others?
</P>
<P>
   A:A fear, I think.
</P>
<P>
   Q:What is the trait you most deplore in yourself?
</P>
<P>
   A:A fear, definitely.
</P>
<P>
   Q:Which living person do you most admire?
</P>
<P>
   A:Nelson Mandela.
</P>
<P>
   Q:In a movie about your life, who stars?
</P>
<P>
   A:Cuba Gooding Jr. He's great!
</P>
<P>
   Q:Who's your favorite hero of movies?
</P>
<P>
   A:That's hard. I don't really have one. My favorite hero,
period, is Martin Luther King Jr. I loved what he stood for. He was
a peaceful warrior. Something I aspire to be.
</P>
<P>
   Q:What is the quality you most like in a woman?
</P>
<P>
   A:I like her to be strong-willed. But I think the quality I find
most attractive about a woman, before strong-willed even, is when
she has ownership of her strength as a woman.
</P>
<P>
   Q:What is the quality you most like in a man?
</P>
<P>
   A:When he admits that women are superior!
</P>
<P>
   Q:What or who is the greatest love of your life?
</P>
<P>
   A:My current. Oh, I shouldn't have said that, because ``my
current'' sounds like there'll be another one along soon. The
greatest love of my life? I'm with her right now. We've been
together about a year and a half.
</P>
<P>
   Q:What do you see when you look in the mirror?
</P>
<P>
   A:My soul, on a good day. On a bad day, nothing.
</P>
<P>
   Q:How do you blow off steam?
</P>
<P>
   A:Tennis. I also spend a lot of time on the computer, writing,
putting stuff up on my own Web site.
</P>
<P>
   Q:What's the best rumor about yourself that you've ever heard?
</P>
<P>
   A:That the scars on my face were the result of some kind of
native ritual.
</P>
<P>
   Q:But didn't you start that rumor?
</P>
<P>
   A:There was a point early in my career when whatever people
wanted to believe, they got. So, yes, I confess, I allowed people
to believe that nonsense.
</P>
<P>
   Seal
</P>
<P>
   Joan Jones opens. 8 p.m. Saturday $26-$36.50. Chastain Park
Amphitheatre, 4668 Stella Drive N.W. 404-249-6400.
</P>
