<DOCNO> NYT19990603.0321 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-03 19:25 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A2085 &Cx1f; kan-z
r v &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-BC-KAN-BUDGET-KAN &LR;      06-03 0405
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BC-KAN-BUDGET-KAN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
   
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Kansas City Star plans to move the following stories for use
by clients of the NYTimes News Service for AMs and PMs of Friday,
June 4. If you have any questions, please call Dennis Boone on the
Star's News Desk at (816) 234-4758.
</P>
<P>
   IRE _ Investigative Reporters and Editors convention begins in
earnest on Friday. We examine the state of investigative journalism
after slipping on the Chiquita banana peel, CNN's gaffe on nerve
gassing our troops in Vietnam, and other media blunders of the past
year. Also will look at some of the good things journalism has
accomplished this year and the big names coming to town for the
convention. By Matt Campbell.Story will move in the ``a'' category.
</P>
<P>
   WATER _ Black ministers, union workers and others angered by The
Star's revelations about plans for a city Water Department takeover
are expected to storm City Hall today and demand answers from Mayor
Kay Barnes during the council meeting. They also may call for U.S.
Attorney Steve Hill to launch an investigation. This is Barnes'
first test on how she handles angry constituents. Gromer Jeffers.
Story will move in the ``a'' category.
</P>
<P>
   FUEL _ Fuel summit concludes in a ``no-decision''; the governors
of Missouri and Kansas will get summaries of various points of view
expressed at the two-day session, but no clear recommendation on
what to do about the metro's pollution-highway construction
conundrum. By Matt Schofield. Story will move in the ``a''
category.
</P>
<P>
   DIGIT _ Telephone callers in the Kansas City area on Saturday
will begin a six-month test run of using area codes when making
local calls across the state line. By Eric Palmer. Story will move
in the ``f'' category.
</P>
<P>
   TWA _TWA Machinists union members in Kansas City will vote on
the airline's final contract offer next week. Plus details on the
contract. By Randolph Heaster. Story will move in the ``f''
category.
</P>
<P>
   LUKE _ Cardiovascular Consultants, a doctors group, will manage
St. Luke's Mid-America Heart Institute under an agreement that's
expected to be signed about July 1. By Julius Karash. Story will
move in the ``f'' category.
</P>
<P>
   HILL04 _ Hillcrest Bank of Overland Park acquires a Wichita
bank. By Charles Crumpley. Story will move in the ``f'' category.
</P>
<P>
   HEASTER-COLUMN _ Economics column by JERRY HEASTER. Story will
move in the ``f'' category.
</P>
