VALDEZ-COLUMN (Phoenix) - Imagine you were an anthropologist
visiting from another planet. It wouldn't take you long to assess
the significance of female breasts in our culture: They are for
marketing and men. But despite the evidence in popular culture,
breasts are not primarily tools for profit or pleasure. They are
designed to feed babies. And they are so good at it that a pair of
