settlement of Kiryat Sefer, on Thursday. On a ``day of rage,''
organized by Yasser Arafat's Palestinian Authority to exert
pressure on Israel's prime minister-elect Ehud Barak to freeze
settlement building, Palestinians clashed with Israeli soldiers in
the West Bank and Gaza Strip. (Rina Castelnuovo/New York Times
Photo) LITE
</P>
<P>
   (NYT2) HEBRON, West Bank -- June 3, 1999 --
MIDEAST-PALESTINIANS-2, 6-3 -- Palestinians waving flags stand
opposite Israeli soldiers near the Israeli settlement of Beth
Hadassah on Thursday. On a ``day of rage,'' organized by Yasser
Arafat's Palestinian Authority to exert pressure on Israel's prime
