become a smaller part of the King operation. (Stephen Crowley/New
York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT30) KINGSVILLE, Texas -- June 3, 1999 -- ADV. FOR SUN., JUNE
6 -- KING-RANCH-1, 6-3 -- Stephen Kleburg, the last descendant of
Richard King to run the King Ranch, was dismissed last year by the
ranch's professional manager. Kleburg stood in front of a portrait
of his father. Traditional ranching activities have been a
diminishing part of the King Ranch's business, as Americans have
reduced their consumption of beef and as more profitable uses have
been found for the land, from oil drilling to quail hunting to
tourism. (Stephen Crowley/New York Times Photo)
